38 weeks pregnant 🤰🏽 and serving fitness. DAY 1 THICC CHALLENGE QUEEENS! Good luck to all my @WBKfit girls starting our 8 week challenge today! To all you girls still thinking about it - here is a lil sneak peek into today's workout. LINK IN BIO FOR LAST MIN SIGN UPS - LET'S DO THIS!!!

1A. Romanian Deadlifts 3x10
1B. Banded Lateral Walks 3x10 each

2A. Barbell Hip Thrust 3x10
2B. Dumbbell Reverse Lunges 3x10 each

3A. Single Leg Hip Thrust (Dumbbell) 3x10 each
3B. Kneeling Banded Kickbacks 3x10 each

4. Banded Leg Press 3x15

Core Finisher (3 rounds, 60s rest between rounds):
5A. Dead Bug x20
5B. Plank Alternating Hip Drops x10 each
5C. Russian Twists x20

Link in bio to join the challenge. Let's build your hourglass and best slim thicc bod yet!

node.text: I always thought I would 100% stick to working out consistently when I got pregnant (before I actually got here) lol… didn’t exactly turn out that way but I did what I could and that’s all that matters! I definitely lost a lot of muscle in my legs and booty, which was replaced by some fat but that’s totally okay with me… I love it here. with the help of my @wbkfit 12 week fit mama to be pregnancy workout plan, it atleast made it a lot easier to stick to a schedule. for all my expecting mamiiiii’s I got you! hit the link in my bio 🤍
